Sentencas: The Nb-doped lanthanum strontium ferrite perovskite oxide La0.8Sr0.2Fe0.9Nb0.1O3- (LSFNb) is evaluated as an anode material in a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Niobium Doped Lanthanum Strontium Ferrite as A Redox-Stable and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The effects of Nb partial substitution in the crystal structure, the electrical conductivity, and the valence of Fe ions are studied.
Titulo: Niobium Doped Lanthanum Strontium Ferrite as A Redox-Stable and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: LSFNb exhibits good structural stability in a severe reducing atmosphere at 800 degrees C, suggesting that high-valent Nb can effectively promote the stability of the lattice structure.
Titulo: Niobium Doped Lanthanum Strontium Ferrite as A Redox-Stable and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The concentration of Fe2+ increases after Nb doping, as confirmed by X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy.
Titulo: Niobium Doped Lanthanum Strontium Ferrite as A Redox-Stable and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of a thick Sc-stabilized zirconia (ScSZ) electrolyte-supported single cell reached 241.6mWcm(-2) at 800 degrees C with H-2 as fuel.
Titulo: Niobium Doped Lanthanum Strontium Ferrite as A Redox-Stable and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The cell exhibited excellent stability for 100h continuous operation without detectable degeneration.
Titulo: Niobium Doped Lanthanum Strontium Ferrite as A Redox-Stable and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Scanning electron microscopy clearly revealed exsolution on the LSFNb surface after operation.
Titulo: Niobium Doped Lanthanum Strontium Ferrite as A Redox-Stable and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Meanwhile, LSFNb particles agglomerated significantly during long-term stability testing.
Titulo: Niobium Doped Lanthanum Strontium Ferrite as A Redox-Stable and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Impedance spectra suggested that both the LSFNb anode and the (La0.75Sr0.25)(0.95)MnO3-/ScSZ cathode underwent an activation process during long-term testing, through which the charge transfer ability increased significantly.
Titulo: Niobium Doped Lanthanum Strontium Ferrite as A Redox-Stable and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Meanwhile, low-frequency resistance (R-L) mainly attributed to the anode (80%) significantly increased, probably due to the agglomeration of LSFNb particles.
Titulo: Niobium Doped Lanthanum Strontium Ferrite as A Redox-Stable and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The LSFNb anode exhibits excellent anti-sulfuring poisoning ability and redox stability.
Titulo: Niobium Doped Lanthanum Strontium Ferrite as A Redox-Stable and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: These results demonstrate that LSFNb is a promising anode material for SOFCs.
Titulo: Niobium Doped Lanthanum Strontium Ferrite as A Redox-Stable and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
